extends java.lang.Object
    Kuba Gasiorowski, kgasiorowski, 109776237, kuba.gasiorowski@sbu.edu Homework #4 Recitation 03 Rec TA: Ka Wing Fong Grading Ta: Zhichuang Sun Represents a node in a directory tree. Can be either a directory or a file.

      • addChild

        public void addChild(DirectoryNode node)
              throws NotADirectoryException,
                     FullDirectoryException
        Adds the given node into this node's children if it has space and if it is a directory.
        Preconditions:
        This node is not a file. There is at least one empty position in the children of this node.
        Postconditions:
        DirectoryNode node has been added as a child of this node, or an exception has been thrown.
        Parameters:
        node - the new node to add to this node's children
        Throws:
        NotADirectoryException - indicates that this node is a file
        FullDirectoryException - indicates that this node has no room to store more children
